<subSubSection id="0E080201CD8D7DED371240B3235E0249" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" type="description">
<paragraph id="8C836FC137EE3AF53C2485AAF443B822" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1DB9FF93FE20556CCD2F63511123369" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
Male (holotype) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="34E83BFEBCD7995489BD789F9AB9BF65" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
A-D, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A585C1120B9F3EB0B990C5DE6F017AC" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7859581" captionText="Figure 2. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678144" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">2</figureCitation>
and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F3E1416BE17D44E116D7627B3FD34FEB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
A-C). Total length 2.92: carapace 1.36 long, 1.07 wide, width/length 0.79; abdomen 1.56 long, 0.85 wide. Carapace oval, reddish-brown, with large dark markings on middle and rear; thoracic groove absent and fovea indistinct (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="83EEB5FD03A70F27E90DB4BB9C816218" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
A). Ocular area black; AER and PER recurved in dorsal view, AER slightly procurved in front view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="07193A72D11628E5CC03CA0179A69794" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
C, D). Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.07, ALE 0.07, PME 0.04, PLE 0.07; AME-AME 0.04, AME-ALE 0.01, ALE-ALE 0.18, PME-PME 0.10, PME-PLE 0.05, PLE-PLE 0.28, ALE-PLE 0.05. OAW 0.37, CRW 0.53, OAW/CRW 0.70. CRW/carapace width 0.50. MOA 0.16 long, front width 0.17, back width 0.20. Clypeus height 0.14. Chilum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03FCF92B18C164B3ED9688FD1E3B5DE1" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
D) semicircular, sclerotized and dark brown. Chelicerae reddish-brown, anterior spines absent, with two promarginal and two retromarginal teeth. Endites brown. Labium dark brown and as wide as long (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="491CCB348D338DE676D3F42725E6BBDB" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
B). Sternum yellowish-brown, longer than wide, with dark margins and dark ribbed pattern in middle, precoxal triangles and intercoxal sclerites distinct (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="10007A86F8E609F4FFFEEC791FC688BC" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
B). Leg I dark brown, with broad white band on 2/3 of tibia distally; legs II-IV light yellow, with balck stripes present on both sides of femora, patellae, tibiae and metatarsi. Measurements of legs: leg I 3.23 (0.93 + 0.37 + 0.77 + 0.64 + 0.52), II 3.01 (0.84 + 0.35 + 0.65 + 0.63 + 0.54), III 2.81 (0.77 + 0.34 + 0.58 + 0.61 + 0.51), IV 4.21 (1.14 + 0.14 + 0.92 + 1.00 + 0.74). Leg formula: 4123. Leg spination: tibiae: I plv 4 rlv 4, II plv 4 rlv 3; metatarsi: I-II plv 1 rlv 1. Abdomen long oval, black; anterior 2/3 with a narrow dorsal scutum and two pairs of inconspicuous transverse white bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="53BCD2FA08D6E140CA5CA27C6D95BA3F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="287401D55EE229EC9C072FA2545F9BAD" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
Palp as illustrated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="48AC39C776DCCF7BB51B6BEA5D5183B9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7859581" captionText="Figure 2. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678144" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">2</figureCitation>
and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1C648FC2AA5E7A5118F4B65FBA48AB5D" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
A-C). Femur with a cup-shaped retrolateral distal boss; patellar and tibial apophyses absent. Tegulum pyriform, with an ovate subapical protrusion; sperm duct U-shaped and short, only present in apical half of tegulum. Embolus beak-shaped, with sharp tip pointed retrolaterally. Cymbium apically with a tuft of thick, flat setae around the apex of embolus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35508B1148BCEA6E516310E15F2D1C34" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
Female (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9AB6F18449B070EEE506A247E64C48F4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
E-H, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="46BCEEA19A9B541FF52D6BE12320C708" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7859585" captionText="Figure 3. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A epigyne, ventral view; B vulva, dorsal view; C female tibia I, prolateral view; D same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678145" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">3</figureCitation>
and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E629D32E6772D24ADAEFC1BF7C5ACC76" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
D-E). Total length 3.61: carapace 1.42 long, 1.10 wide, width:length = 0.77; abdomen 2.19 long, 1.35 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.06, ALE 0.07, PME 0.04, PLE 0.07; AME-AME 0.05, AME-ALE 0.01, ALE-ALE 0.19, PME-PME 0.13, PME-PLE 0.05, PLE-PLE 0.31, ALE-PLE 0.06. OAW 0.39, CRW 0.69, OAW: CRW= 0.57. CRW: carapace width = 0.62. MOA 0.17 long, front width 0.17, back width 0.21. Clypeus height 0.12, 2 times AME diameter. Leg I dark brown, with broad white band on two-thirds of tibia distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="42EE508C09B1276C2667DF70C30A897B" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7859585" captionText="Figure 3. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A epigyne, ventral view; B vulva, dorsal view; C female tibia I, prolateral view; D same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678145" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">3</figureCitation>
C-D). Measurements of legs: leg I 3.69 (1.06 + 0.42 + 0.89 + 0.69 + 0.63), II 3.38 (0.98 + 0.37 + 0.76 + 0.66 + 0.61), III 3.11 (0.85 + 0.37 + 0.66 + 0.68 + 0.55), IV 3.83 (1.33 + 0.42 + 0.11 + 1.17 + 0.80). Leg formula: 4123. Leg spination: tibiae: I plv 5 rlv 4, II plv 4 rlv 3; metatarsi: I-II plv 1 rlv 1. Abdomen with conspicuous transverse white bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C0FF41A078F5728E1634C4FE423631A5" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7818857" captionText="Figure 1. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male habitus, dorsal view; B same, ventral view; C male ocular area, dorsal view; D male cephalothorax, frontal view; E female habitus, dorsal view; F same, ventral view; G female ocular area, dorsal view; H female cephalothorax, frontal view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667853" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">1</figureCitation>
E). Other somatic characters as in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC37C95C3206977278B2626A2F4C8C41" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
Epigyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E568CD1A8A8541B5EB8BF9F079353068" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7859585" captionText="Figure 3. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A epigyne, ventral view; B vulva, dorsal view; C female tibia I, prolateral view; D same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678145" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">3</figureCitation>
A and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B3D59757507CFEBE99968BBF30F32508" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
D): poorly sclerotized, spermathecae and copulatory ducts visible through translucent cuticle; copulatory openings small, located posteriorly, separated by about four spermatheca lengths. Vulva (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9F97BD7F6683FBF8EA23100A6C1779B0" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7859585" captionText="Figure 3. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A epigyne, ventral view; B vulva, dorsal view; C female tibia I, prolateral view; D same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678145" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">3</figureCitation>
B and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A0CD39EAC63B574010273E8C8E7790FF" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
E): copulatory ducts directed laterally, anterior part hook-shaped; bursae large, kidney-shaped, with sclerotized bases; spermathecae long oval, close to each other; connecting tubes curved, connecting bursal bases and spermathecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5E8E0928F45217860AEAA4EE5DEF41EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0FED803B7A5CD4007525D79C2012A969" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="509FFF6F6C16C87B72BF9B06472181F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="60A1D7CF3C4B341D6C9D7AFA0D779787" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" class="Arachnida" family="Phrurolithidae" genus="Plynnon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plynnon zborowskii" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zborowskii">
<emphasis id="D2049BDC56FF959A2886FD52E0A41B31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">Plynnon zborowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a pyriform palpal tegulum and the long oval spermathecae that have similar position, but can be distinguished by: 1) embolus beak-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C73A5AA016D60BE2F5EF90317CF44B50" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7859581" captionText="Figure 2. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678144" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">2</figureCitation>
B and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B091F8DF15EC0C9ACD8F3742C18F99F9" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
B) vs. S-shaped in 
<taxonomicName id="09705686DBD490AD07EF3DBB158B0C13" genus="P." lsidName="P. zborowskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" rank="species" species="zborowskii">
<emphasis id="3AF3434F4549A8AE16603E8A27F81823" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">P. zborowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="97EF9A2F329654EF511AA833301B41EC" author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" refId="B7806358" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L., 2001. Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic]). Brill, Leiden" title="Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic])" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 440, fig. 718); 2) femoral distal boss of male palp present (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5ECA4E1EF3A0401600DB238C86C6DAE4" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F7859581" captionText="Figure 2. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678144" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">2</figureCitation>
C and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2FAD44446722E3D62F20936B9D66D809" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
C) vs. absent in 
<taxonomicName id="384C190D07AB22EF47A59F61139F9BCF" genus="P." lsidName="P. zborowskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" rank="species" species="zborowskii">
<emphasis id="D9F9BC34AB7EB877DE1910973976B13A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">P. zborowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0668C75ED0D869B9D181663F91B15AB9" author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" refId="B7806358" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L., 2001. Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic]). Brill, Leiden" title="Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic])" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 440, fig. 719); 3) the position of copulatory openings is almost parallel to the bases of the bursae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D66BC15CF827BA52E0D5A32BBD1103DA" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7859585" captionText="Figure 3. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A epigyne, ventral view; B vulva, dorsal view; C female tibia I, prolateral view; D same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678145" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">3</figureCitation>
A and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8513BC65492816CFF42E19B0CE49187D" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
D) vs. noticeably posterior in 
<taxonomicName id="7836AABF9860904DA29E839FFC4B8E51" genus="P." lsidName="P. zborowskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" rank="species" species="zborowskii">
<emphasis id="46CE6882D907E065640E05A69FA03FF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">P. zborowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="786D46692F307077F36B1A104D3B6CFE" author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" refId="B7806358" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L., 2001. Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic]). Brill, Leiden" title="Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic])" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 440, fig. 720); 4) the middle part of the copulatory ducts almost straight (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B2252B78711E8DE0DCD136F282C9939F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F7859585" captionText="Figure 3. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A epigyne, ventral view; B vulva, dorsal view; C female tibia I, prolateral view; D same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678145" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">3</figureCitation>
B and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="998395E3AAC3FE029EB79D6563EFB238" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F7818865" captionText="Figure 4. Plynnon aduncum sp. n. A male left palp, prolateral view; B same, ventral view; C same, retrorolateral view; D epigyne, ventral view; E vulva, dorsal view. Abbreviations: B, bursa; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; CT, connecting tube; E, embolus; FDB, femoral distal boss; S, spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667855" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">4</figureCitation>
E) vs. folded in 
<taxonomicName id="A1852F7688DE649161FDEB62DBBC68DA" genus="P." lsidName="P. zborowskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" rank="species" species="zborowskii">
<emphasis id="43F372122B8FFC22B31EAD93F742D283" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">P. zborowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1466967306AD3AA03D80EC5622364536" author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" refId="B7806358" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L., 2001. Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic]). Brill, Leiden" title="Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae [sic])" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold 2001</bibRefCitation>
: 440, fig. 720).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2392E968F2A72359848F80AAB0639F2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="44F3DBED1484536DC0141A8BE9F1E4C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41227A1CB8BA84C39BAEFEBAD1435EA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
The specific name is a Latin adjective meaning 
<normalizedToken id="ADD2CA233CDE861AE20519969B17A7C3" originalValue="“hooked”">&quot;hooked&quot;</normalizedToken>
. It refers to the front part of copulatory ducts curved as hook-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="317FA7D7FD6CB1DC4221A5A2FF4BB56A" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6E3AAFEC80AF475560648C6F39590BBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7EAF5DE77D721D6905BC815B8EFB3C20" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">
Known only from the type locality (Yunnan, China) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="906272167D3769D89FE070BBF1EBDE03" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F7859644" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution of Plynnon aduncum sp. n. (red circle)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e85029.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678174" pageId="0" pageNumber="85029">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
